Commentary.Commentary: So South Africa have 284 on the board. The pitch has some assistance for the bowlers and it will not be an easy task for the England players. How will the openers fare? Join us after a brief break to find out.

It was a controversial decision to bowl first but the English bowlers backed their captain's decision and were good with the cherry in hand. Broad and Sam Curran were the stars with the ball. The pair scalped 8 wickets equally amongst themselves. Archer was good in patches but was pretty inconsistent. James Anderson was good as well but got just a wicket on his 150th Test. All in all the visitors will be happy with their performance.

So the innings has lasted just under 10 minutes on Day 2! The hosts have put up a fighting total after struggling at 111/5. All the batters except Quinton de Kock failed to get going after getting starts. De Kock's 95 along with supports from Dwaine Pretorius and Vernon Philander ensured that South Africa reach a score close to 300.

OUT! Caught! There is a spike on Ultra Edge and Philander has to go. A good length ball which is outside off and it is shaping further away from Philander. He pokes at it away from his body and ends up nicking behind. Buttler catches it and celebrates. The umpire raises his finger but Philander goes for the review. Probably because it is there at his disposal. Don't think it is going to save him though. Here comes the replay. The front foot is okay. There seem to be a deflection as the ball passes the bat and the Ultra Edge clearly detects it. The decision stays OUT and that is the end of the innings for South Africa. 284/10 IT IS.

Given caught behind by Philander reviews quickly. Surely some noise there. Let's see where it is coming from. Front foot is fine. There is a deflection as the ball passes the bat. Here comes the Ultra Edge. Clear edge and that will be end of the innings.

A better throw would've made things interesting but two runs for Philander and South Africa nonetheless. A good length ball just around off, Philander pushes it through covers and looks to take two. Nortje is little slow in responding and the throw from sweeper cover comes but Broad is in front of the stumps to collect. He ends up disturbing the stumps with his hands.

We are ready to begin Day 2. The England players are out in the middle. Vernon Philander will be joined by Anrich Nortje. Stuart Broad will finish his over.

Almost an even first day in SuperSport Park. However, England would've been slightly disappointed after their effort in dismissing the tail. After removing half the side just over 100, England faced resistance from Quinton de Kock and Dwaine Pretorius. The duo added quickfire 87 runs. After their dismissal, Philander made sure they added further important runs. Broad struck on the last ball of the day to remove Rabada and finish the day on a high. Now, on Day 2, England would want to get rid of the last man as early as possible while the hosts would look to score a few quick runs to take their total around 300. Let's see what is on the cards. Welcome to our coverage for Day 2.

So, 277/9 is how we finish Day 1 here in Centurion. The pitch has something on offer for both, the batters as well as the bowlers. But as the saying goes, don't judge a pitch before both sides have bowled on it. So will South Africa be able to add any runs to their overnight score or will England get the final wicket early and come to bat? Join us to find out which way the match turns on Day 2. Join us on Friday, 27th December 2019 at 1000 local (0800 GMT) to find out. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

England will be happy with their efforts but they had their struggles as well. They got off to a dream start as James Anderson struck gold on the very first ball of the game in his 150th Test. Broad who has been struggling fought well to get 3 wickets and ended the day on a positive note. Jofra Archer struggled too but will be happy to get into the wickets column. However, the real star of the day was Sam Curran. In all honesty, whenever it looked like South Africa were getting on top, Sam got his skipper the breakthrough they were looking for. He finished the day with 4 wickets and ensured England are slightly ahead heading into Day 2.

South Africa after being put into bat got off to a horrible start losing Dean Elgar on the very first ball of the Test. Zubayr Hamza and Aiden Markram then tried to steady the ship but after a 32-run stand Markram too joined his opening partner back in the pavilion. Hamza looked good for his 39 but could not convert his start. Faf too failed to make the most of the start he got. Rassie van der Dussen failed to make a mark on his debut. Quinton de Kock though walked out with intent and started counter-attacking as England were getting on top.  He put up a vital 87-run partnership with debutant Dwaine Pretorius. The latter fell against the run of play but Quinton continued his good work. He put up a gritty 47-run stand with Philander but he fell 5 short of a very well-deserved ton. Keshav Maharaj and Rabada ate away a few balls but both of them departed before stumps but ensured that the hosts walk out to bat at least for a ball on Day 2.

Perfect way for England to end the day. Broad strikes on the very last ball of the day. End of a  gritty, fighting and even Day 1 of the Test. The series has started off showing us that it is not going to be a walk in the park for either side.

Another ball outside off, de Kock makes second leave of the over.

FOUR! Just short! Floated on off, Pretorius lofts it over long off. It looks like the ball hits the ropes on the full but the umpires go upstairs to check if that has hit the rope or not. Replay rolls in and after a few views the third umpire says it is a boundary to the on-field umpire as the ball hit the turf just before the ropes.
Floated delivery on off, Quinton drives it through covers. The batsmen take a run.
Floated delivery on off, Quinton punches it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Kock blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Quinton taps it to point.
Tossed up delivery on off, de Kock plays it to point.

There it is. Fifty for Quinton de Kock, his 18th in Tests. A brilliant hand this from Quinton. A short ball on middle, de Kock pulls it towards mid-wicket and takes a run to reach the landmark. Brilliant attacking innings and he would be looking to reach the three figure mark from hereon.
Fuller around off, pushed to cover by de Kock.
Full and on off, pushed towards cover for a single. 50-run stand is up between the two and these runs have come in quick time and against the run of play.
Outside off, it is left alone.

Edgy FOUR! Now the edge flies to the fence off Pretorius' bat. A full ball outside off, Pretorius goes for the drive away from the body. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the third man fence.
In the channel outside off, Pretorius makes a leave by covering his stumps.
Flighted delivery on off, Quinton offers a forward defense on this one.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Kock drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
What was that! Another ball outside off, a tossed up one too. De Kock goes for the sweep again but the ball takes the outside edge and goes over the leaping Ben Stokes. A couple of runs.
Floated delivery on middle, de Kock sweeps it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on middle, de Kock sweeps it towards the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on off, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball around off, pushed to point.
Fuller and around off, pushed through point for a single.

EDGY FOUR! Another one off the outside edge! 150 comes up for South Africa. Another fuller ball which is just outside off. De Kock once again goes for the drive. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the third man fence, past the diving attempt of the gully fielder. 9th boundary for de Kock.
Slightly short and just outside off this time, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.

FOUR! Up and over! De Kock is no mood to calm down as he once again throws his willow to this fuller ball outside off. This time the ball takes the outside edge and it flies over the slip cordon and into the fence.
Outside off, de Kock offers no shot to this one.
James Anderson is back on. 11-4-25-1 are his figures so far.
Floated on off, de Kock plays it towards cover and keeps the strike with a single.

Just shot! It has not carried. Slightly quicker from Root around off. De Kock looks to defend but the ball spins away from him. It takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Ben Stokes there looks to take it on the full, inches above the ground but looks like it has fallen short judging by Root and Stokes' reaction. The umpire takes it upstairs with the soft signal as 'Not Out'. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball fell just short as it goes into the hands of Stokes.
Has that carried? Looking at the England players reaction it looks like it hasn't but let's see what the replays have to say.
Follows the maximum with an easy single towards cover.
SIX! Oh that is a monster. Floated on middle and off, Pretorius who is known for his T20 exploits shows what he is capable of as he hammers it over the long on fence, using the arc for a biggie.
Tossed up delivery outside off, de Kock drives it through covers. The batsmen take a single.
Floated delivery on middle, Pretorius drives it through mid on for a single.

INSIDE EDGE AND FOUR! Length ball outside off, De Kock throws his bat at it looking to slam it through point. The ball though takes the lower half of his bat and goes to the right of the keeper. Buttler is wrong-footed and he dives but he cannot save it. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Good length delivery on middle, de Kock blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Very well controlled pull from de Kock. Curran bangs it in short, Quinton picks it up early and gets on his back foot. He pulls it with control and power through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, de Kock defends it out.
On a good length on off, Quinton defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it to covers.
Floated delivery on middle, de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pretorius flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

In the air... but Anderson cannot reach there. The bait of coming to bowl almost paid off for Root. A flighted ball just outside off, inviting de Kock for the drive. He obliges and looks to slam it over long off. But the bat turns in his hand and he ends up lobbing the shot high towards mid off. Anderson hares from covers to get under the ball but he cannot get there and ends up missing out the chance of dismissing de Kock.
Outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Poor start from Root as he dishes this way to outside off. De Kock reaches it out and guides it to third man fence.
England have no front line spinner in this game so skipper Joe Root will roll his arm over. He is a wicket-taker and can be handy with the ball.
Shortish around off, Pretorius taps it towards the off side off the back foot.

Huge appeal for LBW but it dies down quickly. A fullish length ball on the pads, Pretorius looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. They appeal but the umpire says not out. Hawk Eye comes in and shows that it was pitching outside leg. So a good call once again from England skipper to not go for the review.
Around off, it is defended.
Loose from Pretorius. Curran goes fullish and outside off, inviting the batter for the drive. Pretorius does that and drives away from his body. He once again makes no connection.
Around off and middle, pushed to point.

Brilliant line and length from Curran. Another good length ball that pitches on middle and shapes away nicely. Pretorius looks to drive but makes no connection as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.

Drinks Break! Around 3 hours of play has been done and all the three hours have belonged to the visitors. England have sent half the South African side back in the hut and have their back against the wall. Quinton de Kock is looking good but he needs a partner to hand around with him. Can the debutant, Dwaine Pretorius be that man who can support the South African wicket-keeper and take his side out of troubled waters?
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.

Another nice drive from de Kock. A full ball outside off, de Kock drills it through covers. Denly from third man hares after the ball and makes a diving stop. The umpires are not sure if the attempt is clean as they refer it upstairs. The third umpire checks multiple replays and then deems it in the favour of the fielding side.
In the channel outside off. de Kock makes a leave.
Around off, defended towards mid off.
Outside off, this time de Kock shoulders arms.
Broad starts the over by going full and outside off. He has seen de Kock going for the drive and that's why he tempts him there. Quinton though lets it go to the keeper
On middle, it is defended.
Full ball on off, pushed to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Pretorius drives it to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Pretorius drives it to point.
On a good length on middle, Pretorius looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.

FOUR! De Kock seems to be playing on different surface. An overpitched ball alright but it still needs to be put away. He leans into the shot and slams this through covers. It whistles to the fence. Fourth boundary for de Kock in no time. However, end of a successful over by Broad.
Fuller and outside off, driven to the fielder at short extra cover.
Pretorius is off the mark straightaway. A good length ball on middle, it is worked towards square leg for a single.
Dwaine Pretorius walks out to bat in his first outing in Tests. With half the side back in the hut and Broad having his tail up, he will have to justify his selection with the bat.

OUT! Gone this time as the ball finds the edge this time. Broad follows the ripper with another one. He once again lands this one just around off. The ball once again shapes a hint away as du Plessis pokes at it by coming half forward. The ball this time takes the outside edge and goes to Root at first slip once again. The English skipper makes no mistake and takes the catch with ease. Faf departs after making a start and with it, half the side is back in the hut.
Absolute jaffa from Broad! Lands this one on a good length and on closer to off pole. The ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge of du Plessis.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Length ball on off, de Kock punches it through extra cover and gets a couple to get through the over. Expensive from Sam Curran, 14 off it.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over and de Kock is pouncing on all the mistakes from Curran. Once again Sam goes wide outside off, de Kock slashes it with ease and power through point for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, de Kock blocks it.
Length ball on off, de Kock looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat.
FOUR! Now on the leg side. Curran is guilty of bowling on de Kock's pads. Quinton's eyes lit up looking at it and he flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! De Kock is off the mark in style. You give a southpaw some width outside off, he will punish you. If you give it to de Kock he will just oblige and hit you the way he wants. Good shot this. Length ball outside off, de Kock just hits it right off the middle through point for a boundary. 100 up for the Proteas.
Good length ball on off, Faf defends it to get through the over.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Another one on the fourth stump line, Faf is happy to watch it carry to the keeper.
Broad goes full and on off. Faf pushes it to mid on.
Once again Broad asks Faf to go for the drive by serving it outside off. Du Plessis has no interest to oblige to Broad's demand.
Broad starts his new spell with a length ball away from the off pole. Du Plessis shoulders arms to it.
Stuart Broad is back on. 8-3-22-1 are his figures so far.

Good length ball outside off, de Kock taps it to the right of the fielder at point. Quinton comes out looking for a quick run but Faf straightaway turns it down. The fielder there makes a very good stop and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Even if he had hit, QdK would have been in.
Back of a length on off, de Kock blocks it.
Length delivery which comes back in on off. Quinton looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball around off, de Kock taps it to point to start his innings.

Quinton de Kock walks in with his side in a very poor situation. 4 already in the hut. He will look to make a handy contribution in this innings to bail the Proteas out. Not gonna be easy against this English bowling lineup though.

OUT! Caught! Yes, Sam can get the breakthrough. The bowling change does the trick for the visitors. The previous one came in to the right-hander, this one moves the other way. It is pitched on off, van der Dussen gets on his front foot and tries to play the classical front foot defense. The ball shapes away and finds the outside edge of the bat and goes straight towards first slip. England skipper, Joe Root there makes no mistake and takes a simple catch. Once again Curran gets the breakthrough. This young man has the knack of doing so and he is doing his reputation no harm. Not a long lasting start to his Test career for Rassie. Just 6 on his maiden outing.
Sam starts with a length delivery which nips back in to the right-hander. Van der Dussen defends it with a straight bat.
Sam Curran is back for the first time in this session. 5-2-8-1, his figures so far. He was troublesome in his first spell. Can he once again get the breakthrough?
Bouncer down the leg side. Du Plessis ducks under it.
Fuller around off, pushed to cover.
In the channel outside off, Faf makes a leave.
Landed on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.

NOT OUT! The decision is overturned and du Plessis survives. Very full and very wide from Archer. Du Plessis chases it and goes for the drive away from the body. He does not make any connection and Buttler behind the wicket catches and appeals along with Archer and the entire slip cordon. The umpire thinks and raises the finger. However, Faf does not think much and signals for the review straightaway. Let's see what the replays show. No problems with the front foot. Now, the Ultra Edge, there is a spike on it as the ball passes the bat but it is not sure from where it is coming from as there is a gap between the bat and ball. Tricky call for the third umpire to make. Not out is the decision from the third umpire then. Looks like a correct call has been made.

Given caught behind but du Plessis goes for the DRS straightaway. Front foot is fine. Is there an outside edge? Could be a massive blow. There is a gap as the ball goes past the bat but there is also a little spike on the Ultra Edge. It might be adjudged Not Out as there is a gap but with the on-field call going the other way, it can go either way as there is a spike. NOT OUT! The on-field umpire reverses his decision and that's a good call as there was a good gap between the bat and ball. So not sure what that spike on Ultra Edge was.
Good length ball around off,  it is blocked off the back foot.
Beaten! Beauty from Anderson. It lands on a fuller length, van der Dussen this time goes for the drive but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge.
Another ball which is outside off and it does not tempt van der Dussen into playing any fancy shot.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Rassie defends it out.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Poor ball to finish the over. Short and wide outside off, du Plessis hammers it through the cover region. It races to the fence in a jiffy.
BEATEN! An absolute jaffa from Archer. Slightly shortish length around off, du Plessis has to play at it. He hops a bit and pokes, luckily the ball goes a hint away and whizzes past the outside edge.
On a good length on leg, du Plessis looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, du Plessis defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Fuller one just outside off, pushed to cover by Rassie.
Shortish around off, van der Dussen stays on the back foot and blocks it towards point.
Full and outside off, pushed to point.

Huge appeal but not out says the umpire. No review from England. A big inside edge there saves van der Dussen. Good call from England to not go for the review. It pitches around off and draws batsman half forward. Rassie pushes at the ball and luckily manages an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball just outside off, Rassie has the stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper.
Landed around off on a good length, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball around off, du Plessis drops his wrists and allows the ball to go the keeper.

On the pads again, van der Dussen looks to work it fine down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes behind and before Buttler can pick the ball, the batters cross ends for a leg bye.
Landed on a good length around off, van der Dussen looks to defend but the ball takes the inside half of the bat and goes to mid on.
Fuller and around off, it is defended.
Fuller and around off, this time Faf pushes it wide of the cover fielder for a single.
On the pads, Rassie tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Another leave as Anderson bowls this one on a good length outside off once again.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball coming into van der Dussen this time. He tucks it towards fine leg to get a run.
Fuller and on off, van der Dussen does well to keep it out.
Full one on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Anderson starts with a poor ball down the leg side. Van der Dussen lets it go to the keeper.
James Anderson to bowl from the other end. 8-2-24-1 are his figures so far.
Bouncer way over the head of ducking du Plessis. End of a top over for South Africa. Solid start of the session for them. 10 from the over.
Fuller one on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over and du Plessis is on the move now. Another ball which is on the stumps line, du Plessis nicely flicks it. The ball races to the deep mid-wicket boundary.
Around off, it is defended.
FOUR! This time clipped through mid-wicket. Another fuller length ball around off and middle, du Plessis uses his wrists and whips it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Archer starts with a ball on the pads of du Plessis. He clips it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.

We are back for the second session. The England players are out in the middle. Faf du Plessis and Rassie van der Dussen will resume their innings for the hosts. Jofra Archer will start the proceedings for the second session.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

Now, Faf du Plessis is battling it out there. He has debutant van der Dussen for company. The duo will look to bail the side out with a solid stand. England, on the other hand, would fancy getting another 2-3 wickets in the next session to take complete control of the game. Will they be able to do so or will they face resistance from the Protea batters? Do join us after the break to find out.

As far as English bowling is concerned, Anderson struck on the very first ball of the over and along with Broad kept things tight in the first hour. Archer too bowled tight lines and did not allow the runs to come freely. Curran in his very first over got the wicket of Markram. Broad then broke another budding stand between Faf and Hamza as he removed Hamza.

James Anderson removed Dean Elgar on the very first ball of the Test match to start the game on a superb note. Markram along with Zubayr Hamza added 32 runs to provide some resistance but Curran in his very first over removed Markram to break the stand. Skipper Faf du Plessis joined Hamza in the middle and the two added 39 runs between them. And when it looked like the Proteas are in for a big stand, Hamza fell to Broad. Du Plessis along with Rassie van der Dussen saw off the remaining few overs to go to Lunch.

A brilliant session for England! They have struck thrice and have not allowed South Africa to score freely either. After winning the toss, Root would've wanted similar returns from his bowlers and they have delivered for him so far.
Length ball on the stumps, van der Dussen defends it with a straight bat to negotiate the final over of the session without any casualty. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
On a good length on middle, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Rassie drives it to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Rassie blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, van der Dussen offers no shot to this one.
Bouncer to end the over. It is around the body, du Plessis sits under it.
Back of a length on off, du Plessis defends it off his back foot.
Good stop. On the pads, du Plessis flicks it but Bairstow at short leg shows good reflex and saves runs for his side.
Archer misses his line and sprays one down the leg side. Faf is not interested in playing that.
Another very good inswinging ball. This time Faf gets a bit of bat on it. Length ball, jagging back in from off. Du Plessis looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

OHH! Just a tad too high maybe. Excellent ball this from Jofra. Steams in and bowls a inswinging length ball around off. Faf looks to defend but the ball comes in viciously and hits him on the thigh pad of his back leg. There is a huge appeal from the English players but the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root has a brief thought about a review but opts against it. Good decision from Joe as Hawk Eye later on shows that the ball was going well over the stumps.
Jofra Archer for the final burst before Lunch. 4-0-25-0 are his figures so far.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery on middle, van der Dussen flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Again outside off, van der Dussen lets it go.
Outside off, Rassie offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, van der Dussen drives it to mid off.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off, du Plessis lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Faf blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, du Plessis offers a calm leave on this one.
On a good length on off, du Plessis defends it to covers.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball around off, it moves away from Faf. He looks to defend it with soft hands but gets an outside edge which goes wide of the man at slip and races away to the fence. Had he played that with hard hands then it might have carried to the fielder there.
Fuller ball on off, pushed to point.

Debutant Rassie van der Dussen is the new man in. Not an ideal condition for him to walk out to bat on his debut. He now has a big task in hand as he will have to bail out his side from trouble along with his skipper.

OUT! Caught next ball. Broad has broken the stand. A good length ball outside off, shaping away from the right-hander.  Hamza can easily leave these but he pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to Stokes at second slip. He pouches it with both hands and sends Hamza packing. Broad and England celebrate. Timely wicket for the visitors.
FOUR! Magnificently timed! Slightly overpitched and Hamza pounces on it nicely. Fuller and outside off, Hamza leans into the drive and creams it through covers. Poses for the cameras there.
Outside off, Hamza does not bother to play at that.
NO BALL! Broad oversteps! Length delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it through mid-wicket. Bairstow chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Hamza keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Hamza defends it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Hamza blocks it well.
Length delivery on leg, Hamza flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Hamza shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it to mid off.
Good length delivery on off, Hamza defends it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Faf flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full delivery on off, du Plessis plays it to covers.
On a length on off, Hamza taps it to point.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hamza looks to defend again but misses it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hamza looks to defend but misses it.
Again outside off, Hamza leaves it alone.
Outside off, Hamza does not bother to play at that.
Full delivery on middle, Hamza drives it towards mid on where Anderson dives and does well to stop it.
Stuart Broad returns for his second spell. 4-1-11-0 from him so far.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, the skipper defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length on middle, Hamza defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it to mid off.
Anderson starts the fresh spell but spraying down the leg side on the first ball. Hamza flicks but makes no connection.
James Anderson is back on. 5-2-17-1 are his figures so far.
Fuller ball way outside off, Faf lets it go to the keeper.
Landed around middle, du Plessis works it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, du Plessis blocks it off the back foot.
Good length ball just outside off, Faf punches it through point for a couple of runs.
Fuller and off, driven wide of the cover fielder for a single. 14 from the over.

EDGY FOUR! Tight line this from Archer. He lands it on a shortish length around off, du Plessis hops and looks to defend but the ball takes the thick outside edge and goes past the diving Ben Stokes. However, it is wide of him and ends up going to the fence. Four for du Plessis and South Africa but Archer won't mind this.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, Hamza nudges it to fine leg and crosses for a run.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Hamza. A good length ball around off, Hamza this time strokes this through mid off. Brilliant followthrough on this shot. Held the pose for the cameras there. 50 up for South Africa.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and wide outside off, Hamza leans into the drive and slams it through covers.
Outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
On a good length around off, du Plessis blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Faf offers a solid defense on this one.
On a good length on off, du Plessis plays it to covers.
Good length delivery on middle, the skipper keeps it out.
On a good length and outside off, du Plessis plays it to covers off the back foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and just outside off, Hamza looks to defend but misses it.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Hamza does well to duck under it.

A bit of indecisiveness from Hamza! Good length ball just around off. It is shaping away from Hamza. He initially looks to defend but then sees that it is going away from his off pole so he retracts on his decision.

FOUR! Don't bother running that was four the moment it left the bat. Poor ball from Archer. Short and wide outside off. Hamza is quick to pounce on it and punches it right off the meat through point for a boundary.
Outside off, Hamza offers no shot to this one.
Archer bowls it on a good length on off, Hamza stands tall and defends it off the back foot.
Full and on off again, du Plessis is solid in his drive towards mid off.
Full and off, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball just outside off, du Plessis taps it towards cover off the back foot.
WIDE! A bouncer this time but it is way over du Plessis. Called wide.
Fuller ball around off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Slightly shortish and outside off, du Plessis allows it go to the keeper.
Curran starts the fresh over post the drinks break by spraying on the pads. Hamza flicks it to fine leg for a run and crosses over.

Drinks Break! Brilliant start for the visitors. They won the toss and decided to bowl and so far that decision is paying off. They have got rid of both the openers and they are also bowling with great intent and vigor. They will look to strike at least one more before Lunch. South Africa need to build a partnership and they will hope that Zubayr Hamza and skipper Faf du Plessis can bat out till Lunch.
On the length around off, du Plessis defends it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.

Just short of Bairstow at short leg. A back of a length ball on middle, du Plessis hops to defend but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and lobs right of Bairstow at short leg. Bairstow dives to his right to catch but the ball ends up just short.
Low full toss outside off, du Plessis reaches out and squeezes it through covers. He is off and running with a couple of runs.
Outside off, left alone.

Quick single! A good length ball around off and middle, Hamza works it towards mid on and takes off for a single. Broad gets there quickly, picks the ball and has a shy at the striker's end. He though misses but du Plessis had made his ground anyway.
Beaten! Peach to finish the over! Superb delivery from the left-armer. Lands it on a good length and around off. Once again makes it shape away from the poke of Faf. Lucky not to edge that one.
This time Curran bowls it full on middle, Faf flicks it nicely but finds mid-wicket.
On off, it is blocked.

Brilliant ball from Curran again. Another ball that lands on middle and off and it shapes just a hint. Faf has to play at it and as he does that, he is squared up. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to the gully fielder.
Back of a length ball on middle, du Plessis hops and blocks it on the leg side.
Good length ball shaping away from the right-hander. Faf lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Flicked nicely! A full ball on middle, Hamza easily flicks it towards deep square leg. The ball races to the fence quickly. Poor ball by Archer to finish the over.
Looses his line and sprays this one down the leg side. Buttler moves to his left and does well to pouch the ball on that side.
Big bouncer on middle, Hamza easily ducks under it.
Wide outside off this one, Hamza lets it be.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander, Hamza defends but the ball takes inside edge and hits on the body.

Brave leave! A brilliant start for Archer though! This wasn't too far away from the top of off. Good line and length. This one pitches just outside off and then comes back in. Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
Change from both the ends. Jofra Archer is introduced into the attack. What do we have in store? Batters watch out for some vicious bouncers here and there.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball on off, it is defended.
South Africa in trouble and out walks their skipper, Faf du Plessis. He will need to play a big innings here as his side need him to take them out of early troubles.

OUT! Caught at mid-wicket. Another soft dismissal. Curran with the knack of picking wickets has struck in the very first over. A good length ball on middle, Markram looks to work it on the leg side. However, he ends up chipping it towards mid-wicket. Bairstow there gets low down and pouches the catch inches above the turf. The good-looking stand is broken.
Edged but just short! A good length ball, closer to the off pole, Markram once again pokes. This time the ball catches the outside edge. It goes to the first slip on the bounce.
Beaten! Curran gets his line and length right and bowls it just outside off, Markram pokes to get beaten.
FOUR! What a welcome for him into the attack.  A fuller ball around off, Markram leans forwards and lofts this over the cover region beautifully. A top shot.
Sam Curran is into the attack.
Good length ball around off, Hamza pushes it towards point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball, this one comes back in nicely. Hamza does well to get his bat down in time to defend.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and just outside off, defended towards mid off.
Good stop! A full ball down the leg side, Hamza looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Buttler behind the wicket dives to his left and stops the ball.
Fuller ball just outside off, Markram has his sticks covered and lets it be.
Landed on middle, it is defended towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Hamza works it wide of the mid on fielder and takes a single.
Bends his back and bowls it short but once again the line is down the leg side which will not trouble Hamza. He ducks under it.
Sprays down the leg side on a length. Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Hamza works it towards deep square leg. Before the fine leg fielder can come around to pick the ball up, the batters get a couple of runs.
Full and on off again, Hamza pushes it right of the short extra cover fielder and takes a quick single.
Goes full on off, Hamza drives it straight to short extra cover.
Good length ball on off, Hamza stays on the back foot and punches it straight to gully.
In the channel outside off, Hamza lets it be.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Confusion but safe... A good length ball around off, Hamza defends it towards point. Markram quickly takes off for the single but Hamza sends him back. Markram is almost halfway in the middle. Denly gets to the ball and fires the throw at the non-striker's end. He misses his shy but Markram had returned well in time.
Good length ball this one which is aimed into the batter. Markram in the defense gets squared up. The ball takes the outer half and goes to the gully fielder on the bounce.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Landed around off, it is defended.
Outside off, Markram is not interested as he shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball around off, Markram makes a solid defensive shot off the back foot.
Broad starts the fresh over by bowling a fuller ball around off, Markram blocks it away.
Hamza makes third consecutive leave to end a good over for South Africa. 11 from the over, all coming from Markram's bat though.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off this time, Hamza lets it go to the keeper.

Three more! This time through the covers. Slightly short and outside off, Markram rides the bounce and punches it nicely. Denly hares after the ball and makes a sliding stop just before the fence. A single saved.

FOUR! Make that two in a row! They say, slash and slash hard. That's what Markram does. A good length ball outside off, he throws the kitchen sink at it. The ball takes the thick outside edge and flies over the leaping second slip fielder.
FOUR! Driven handsomely! Full and wide outside off, inviting the batter to go for the drive. Markram accepts it and creams the drive through covers. It races to the sweeper cover fence in a jiffy.
Good length which is again outside off and Hamza has no problem letting this go to the keeper.
Slightly fuller but once again way outside off, it is Broad this time. Hamza lets it be.
Good length around off, Hamza works it towards mid on and thinks of a run but they decide against it as the ball went to the mid on fielder quickly.
Just behind good length but outside off, Hamza allows it to go to the keeper.
Nicely punched! A slightly fullish ball, Hamza strokes it past mid on and picks a couple of easy runs before the mid on fielder can get to the ball.
Fuller and on off, Markram tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Fullish but once again outside off, Hamza shoulders arms once again. Anderson needs to get closer to off pole and make the batter play.
Around off on a length, Hamza defends it out.
Make that third leave in a row as Zubayr allows this good length ball outside off go to Buttler behind the wicket.
Fuller but very wide outside off, Hamza shows no interest as he shoulders arms.
Good length ball way outside off, Hamza lets it be.
Good length ball around off and middle, it is angled in. Hamza looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the thigh pads.
Fuller and outside off, Markram is not into driving as he lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, Markram makes a leave.
Beaten! Beauty from Broad. A good length ball outside off, shaping away nicely. Markram plays at it but the ball goes away beating the outside edge and to the keeper.
Around off on a length, it is defended.

FOUR! Shot! A fuller ball around off, Markram just comes forward and pushes it defensively. The mid on fielder dives to his left to stop but fails to do so. It races to the fence and Markram is off the mark in a nice fashion.
Archer starts with a fuller ball on middle, Zubayr flicks it to deep square leg and changes end.
Stuart Broad to bowl from the other end.
In the channel outside off, Markram makes a leave. End of the first over and a successful one too.
Good length ball around off, Markram defends it with a straight bat.
On the pads, Hamza works it fine down the leg side for a single.

Edgy FOUR! Hamza is off the mark! Anderson goes full just outside off, Hamza comes forward and defends. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to the third man fence. First boundary off the game! Not the way the hosts would have wanted it to come but they will take it.
Good length ball outside off, Hamza makes a leave.
Zubayr Hamza is the new batsman in, quite early than he would've hoped.

OUT! Caught down the leg side! Wow! What a start! Dean Elgar is out of here on the first ball of the Boxing Day Test. Just a feather down the leg side but Anderson and England won't care. 150th Test for Jimmy and what a start for England. A gentle length ball down the leg side. Elgar looks to tickle it fine off his pads but he can only get a feather behind. Buttler behind the wickets makes no mistake and England are off to a perfect start and well, South Africa, not sure what to say. Such a soft dismissal, this one.

We are all set to begin. The England players are out in the middle. Aiden Markram and Dean Elgar will open the batting for South Africa. James Anderson will start the proceedings for England. Here we go...
The players from both the sides are coming out for the National Anthems first up. First it is for England and then that will be followed by South Africa.

Faf du Plessis, South Africa skipper, says that they expected England to bowl first provided the kind of bowling unit they have. Tells that Day 2 and Day 3 will be good to bat on and then the coming days will see the cracks open up and wicket will get tricky. On Pakistan and England tour, Faf says that lot of things have happened for them but they are still standing and mentions that they're looking forward to the new year. On retired experienced players like Smith, Boucher and Kallis taking important roles in South African Cricket, du Plessis says that these are experienced players and they bring a lot on table for the game of cricket. Tells that they will try to make sure they put on a good performance for the fans.

Joe Root, England captain, says that the decision to bowl first is quite a tricky one but they would like to explore the grass on the wicket. Tells that Leach is unfit and hence the 5-seam attack for them. Talking about Stokes' return, The England skipper says that the time is tough for him right now but he has decided to play this game. On Anderson's 150th Test, Root says that as a fast bowler playing 150 Tests is a massive achievement.

SOUTH AFRICA (PLAYING XI) - Aiden Markram, Dean Elgar, Zubayr Hamza, Rassie van der Dussen (Test DEBUT), Faf du Plessis (C), Quinton de Kock (WK), Dwaine Pretorius (TEST DEBUT), Vernon Philander, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje.
ENGLAND  (Playing XI) - Rory Burns, Dominic Sibley, Joe Denly, Joe Root (C), Ben Stokes, Jonny Bairstow, Jos Buttler (WK), Sam Curran, Jofra Archer, Stuart Broad, James Anderson.
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in the favour of England. THEY WILL BOWL FIRST.

Christmas is over but not the festive season and as long as cricket is concerned, the next day after Christmas is always an important one. Why? Because in Australia and South Africa, both the teams host a Boxing Day Test. One in Australia has already started and the hosts are in a commanding position there. What will happen in this game? Here, South Africa is hosting England for a 4-Test series with the first one starting on the historic Boxing Day. England have a few health issues with several players set to miss out this Test due to illness. For the hosts, Vernon Philander has announced that this series is going to be his last one. How will it pan out for him? How will 150th Test match pan out for James Anderson? We have plenty of questions that need answers. We will have them all in the course of this Test. Stay with us for the Toss and team updates.

So South Africa have a 103 run lead and are comfortably in the command here. England will have to toil hard again and need to stay in the field for more than 90 minutes. Can they strike early and fight their way back in the game? Join us in a while to find out.

A superb bowling display from the hosts. They started off brilliantly and it was a collective bowling effort from them. Vernon Philander was the undisputed star with the ball. He asked question to the English batsmen every time he bowled and also kept things tight. He bowled 14.2 overs and gave away just 16 runs picking up 4 wickets. Kagiso Rabada struggled initially but ended up with 3 wickets. Nortje and Pretorius were good too, picking up 2 and 1 wicket respectively. Maharaj was the only bowler who did not get a wicket but he was very tight in the 4 overs they bowled.

Once again England collapse and after staying on the field for almost 85 overs, the visitors have failed to give their bowlers the rest they would have been looking for. After wrapping up South Africa 10 minutes into the morning. The hosts started off badly losing both the openers early on.  Joe Root and Joe Denly then steadied the ship with a 55-run stand. Root though could not capitalise on their start. Stokes then continued the good work and at 142/3 it looked like England were in the driver's seat. But as has been the story with this English Test side one just cannot be confident. They are used to a collapse and that is what happened. The visitors started losing wickets left, right and centre and from 142/3 they have been bundled out for 181. Giving South Africa a head start of 103 heading into the 3rd innings.

OUT! Knocks over the off stump and England are all out. Outstanding bowling from Philander. He has his fourth. A good length ball on off which goes straight after pitching. Archer looks to defend but misses. The ball goes behind and disturbs the off pole. ENGLAND ARE ALL OUT FOR 181!
Full and on middle from Philander, Archer gets his bat down in time to keep it out.
Beaten! In the channel outside off, Anderson pokes at the ball to get beaten.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
James Anderson walks out at number 11 on his 150th Test. Any runs he will add now will be a bonus.

OUT! Caught at gully! Terrific bowling from Rabada. Bowls a bouncer outside off, Broad can only push it in the hands of Elgar at gully. Bouncer has always troubled Broad and Rabada dished out one to send him back to the pavilion. 9 down and still behind 103.

Fuller and around off, pushed to point for a single.

Full and on off, driven for a couple of runs through covers.

Shortish ball just outside off, Broad taps it off the back foot.
Stuart Broad joins his pace bowling partner Jofra Archer out in the middle.

OUT! Caught behind! Sixth catch of the match and it is a blinder behind the wicket from de Kock. Last recognized batsman is gone now and England are staring at a huge first innings lead. Sharp bouncer around off, Buttler hops to push but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. De Kock throws himself to his right and gobbles the ball with both hands, in front of the first slip. Philander has three and England are 8 down.

A good length ball on middle, Curran flicks but hits it straight to Hamza at short leg. He gets down in time towards his left and pouches it nicely. Another timely wicket for the Proteas. Rabada sprays down the leg side this time. Curran flicks but cannot make any connection.

Good length ball just outside off, defended towards mid off.

Around off, defended off the back foot.
Beaten! Terrific line from Rabada. A good length ball around off, a hint of movement away from the batter is enough to beat the outside edge.

On middle, Curran does well to defend it out off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, pushed to mid off by Curran.
That one kept really low! A full ball outside off, Curran drives away from the body but the ball sneaks through the bat to the keeper who cannot gather the ball cleanly.

We are back for the final session of the day. The South African players are out in the middle. Sam Curran and Jos Buttler will resume their innings for England. Vernon Philander will start the proceedings for the final session of the day.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

South Africa would not be happy with how the first hour of the session played out. They bowled well but were unable to break that partnership. But the second hour saw the hosts get on top and take charge. Debutant Dwaine Pretorius provided his skipper the breakthrough they were desperately looking for. Anrich Nortje then joined the act and his two quick wickets has seen South Africa head into Tea being in the driver's seat. So what do we have in store for the final session? Can England make a comeback or will South Africa wrap it up early in the final session? Join us after the break to find out.

What a brilliant session of Test cricket we have witnessed here in Centurion. The pendulum of this match keeps moving. It looked like England were well and truly on top with Stokes and Denly going along their merry way. The latter got to his fifty and with the score reading 142/3, it looked like England will easily head into Tea with their noses well and truly in front. But as we have witnessed so many times in the recent past, and England collapse was not far away. From 142/3 the visitors found themselves reeling at 150/6. They lost 3 wickets in the space of 16 balls and now find themselves in  a big spot of bother.

On a good length on off, Jos keeps it out.

Sam Curran is in now. Bailed England out on a few occasions when India toured England in 2018. Can he do so here? England would certainly hope so. Two slips, a short leg and a gully fielder placed for him.

OUT! Caught behind! Nortje gets his second wicket of the game and no prizes for guessing who has caught it. It is Quinton de Kock. His 5th catch of the innings and England from a commanding position have their backs against the wall. This is proper Test match wicket. Nortje hits the deck hard on a length at 144 kph. The ball shapes away just a bit. Stokes looks to defend but that little zip troubles him enough to take the outside edge and goes straight into the mitts of Quinton de Kock. The Proteas are up in joy and celebration. England's crisis man is out of here and he is gutted with himself as he knows technically he was well below par on that shot. The visitors trail by 134 and have just 4 wickets in hand now.
Good length delivery on off, Ben defends it out.
On a good length on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.

On a good length on off, Stokes defends it towards point and takes a run.

Jos Buttler is the new batsman in.

OUT! Knocks him over! Nortje is the man who strikes for the first time and half the English side is back to the pavilion. Brilliant line and length this from Nortje. A good length ball from him which pitches outside off and then comes in nicely. Bairstow without any feet movement looks to defend. But the ball keeps low and comes back in to beat the defense of Bairstow. It goes behind and rattles the timber. Bairstow's poor run in Tests in 2019 continues.

Jonny Bairstow joins Ben Stokes out in the middle. He has not been in the best of forms in the longest format of the game with the bat and there have been a lot of talks about it. He needs to play a big innings here to not just justify his selection but also retain his place in this playing 11.

OUT! Caught behind! The Ultra Edge detects a faint inside edge and Denly has to depart. Pretorius gets his debut Test wicket and an important one too as South Africa have broken the partnership. 50 and gone, 6th time this has happened in Tests for Denly. His search for his maiden Test ton continues. A superb ball from Pretorius. It is just ahead of the back of a length. It pitches and then comes back in as Denly comes forward and looks to defend. He misses to do so and the ball goes behind. De Kock takes the catch and makes a confident appeal along with the bowler. The umpire though is unmoved. After a brief chat, South Africa opt for the review and the replays detect the small spike as the ball gets closer to the bat. So, the on-field decision will be overturned.

Is there an edge? The umpire doesn't think so but Faf du Plessis has signaled the 'T'. The front foot is fine. Looks like an inside edge there. Yes, a faint spike is confirmed by the Ultra Edge. Superb review from South Africa.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
What a response from Pretorius. Lands this one on a good length just outside off and makes the batter poke at it.

On middle, Stokes tucks it towards mid-wicket for a run.

Around off, it is defended.

Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it through square leg for a single.

De Kock throws the ball back to the bowler at the non-striker's end but by the time it reaches, Denly is home.
On a good length on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Denly flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Joe leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
FIVE WIDES! Bowls a bouncer down the leg side, Denly does well to duck under it. It goes way past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Denly offers no shot to this one.

Rabada has been not at his best and has leaked runs. Philander from one end has kept things tight but has not got support from the other end. The Proteas need wickets quickly or else these two will add quick runs and take England's total closer to South Africa quickly. Interesting hour awaits.
Restores calmness and defends it off the front foot.

SIX! Two in a row. This one is a flat hit but once again hardly hit. Floated on off, Stokes once again gets down on one knee and slogs it flat over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum. 50-run stand is up between Ben Stokes and Joe Denly.
SIX! Don't bother looking that was six the moment it left the bat. Flighted on off, Stokes gets down on one knee and smashes it over the mid-wicket fence for a big six.

Floated delivery on off, Stokes  blocks it well.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Stokes blocks it off the back foot.
Keshav Maharaj returns.
FOUR BYES! Bowls a bumper, Denly ducks under it. It goes towards Quinton de Kock who jumps and tries to stop by leaping but he can only get a glove on it. It ends up going to the third man fence.
Bowls a bouncer, Denly does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
On a length on middle, Stokes flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Length delivery on off, Denly taps it towards point and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Denly nudges it towards the leg side.
Anrich Nortje replaces Philander. 5-0-23-0 are his figures so far.
On a length on middle, Stokes tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on off, Ben blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Stokes taps it to point.
FOUR! Whipped nicely! Full delivery on middle, Stokes drives it through mid on for a boundary. 100 up for England.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Brilliant from Maharaj at gully. A full ball outside off, Denly drills the drive nicely but Maharaj dives full length to his right to make a half stop. The ball rolls just away and before he can get up and get to the ball, the batters cross.
Bowls it down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Landed on middle, Denly flicks it between mid on and mid-wicket and takes a single.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Denly does well to keep it out.
Fuller ball around off, pushed to cover.
Around off on a length, Denly blocks it out.
On a good length on off, Ben blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Stokes pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Stokes pushes it through mid on. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Stokes offers a solid defense on this one.
On a good length on off, Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Change of ends for Rabada as well. 9-0-44-1, his numbers so far. He has struggled a bit post Lunch. Let's see whether the change of ends does the trick for him.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Flicked nicely! A good length ball on the pads, Denly whips it to mid-wicket. The mid on fielder chases it down and keeps the batters to a couple of runs.

Landed around off on a good length, Denly keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
