Change of ends for Vernon Philander. He has created havoc from the other end. Can he do the same from this side.
FOUR! Over mid off! This time Denly reaches the pitch of this tossed up ball outside off and lofts it over mid off for a boundary. Looking really impressive ever since the first run he got.
On off, Denly keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Full around off, Denly this time skips down the track and looks to go downtown over long on. However, the ball hits the lower part of the bat and goes to mid on who fumbles but no runs costed.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly plays it to point.
Tossed up on off, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Keshav Maharaj to bowl now. Just a over in the first session. A slip and a short leg in place for him.
Around off, it is defended.
3 slips and a gully are in place for Ben Stokes.
Shortish around off, Denly works it behind square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! A short ball outside off, Denly hangs back and guides it between the second slip and gully fielder. It races to the third man fence. Another boundary off Rabada.
Good length ball around off, Denly defends it towards cover off the back foot.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Back of a length ball around off, Denly pulls but finds mid on.
Uppish but safe! Fuller and outside off, Stokes drives away from the body. The ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes to point uppishly. A lot of oohs and aahs from the slip cordon.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Almost chopped on! A good length ball around off, Stokes defends it away from the body. The ball hits the lower part of the willow and balloons near the stumps. Stokes though is aware about it as he looks to keep the ball away. He does not need to do so as it does not go on the stumps anyway.
Fullish ball outside off, asking the left-hander to go for the drive. Stokes though is not interested as he makes a leave by covering his stumps.
Landed on off, Stokes comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, Stokes taps it towards the gully fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball just outside off, Denly tucks it to point once again.
Around off, tapped towards point.

FOUR! Sprays down the leg side and gets the punishment. A ball on the pads on a good length, all Denly has to do is tickle it fine down the leg side. He does that nicely and the ball races to the fine leg fence. Rabada is leaking runs here. Not doing good to his partner who is bowling brilliantly at the other end.
Brilliant from Hamza at gully! A good length ball around off, Denly goes on the back foot and looks to run it down towards third man but Hamza dives to his right and saves runs for his side.
FOUR! Crashed away! Short ball on middle, Denly rocks back and pulls it wide of the long on fence for a boundary.
Make that third leave in a row as Philander dishes out another ball outside off on a length.
Another ball outside off which is shaping away from the left-hander. Stokes has his stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper once again.
Outside off for the left-hander and on a good length, Stokes allows it to go to the keeper.
Philander steams in and once again pulls off from his bowling stride. Has his arms up in apology. Done a couple of times already. Not sure about the reason.
On middle again, Stokes is right behind the line of the delivery to defend.
Landed on middle, it is defended.

The captain is replaced by the vice captain. Ben Stokes, England's new superstar is the new man in. It has been Stokes' year and he has taken his side out of trouble a lot of times. He will once again need to do the same. Can he produce another rabbit out of the hat?

OUT! The England skipper is out of here and it is a body blow for England. Brilliant from Philander once again. Spot on with his line and length once again. Another ball in the channel outside off, Root can easily leave these alone. He though decides to have a poke at it. Joe ends up getting a tickle behind the wicket. De Kock takes the catch and celebrates. The umpire too raises the finger instantly and Root walks off. As he goes to the pavilion, punches his bat. Did all the hard work and then threw it away.
FOUR! Glorious! Overpitched from Rabada and Denly pounces on it. He leans into the shot and creams it through covers.
Around off, it is defended.
Shortish around off again, Root goes on the back foot and taps it towards cover and takes off for a single. Maharaj gets to the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Shortish outside off again, Root hops and pushes it towards point.
On middle, Root defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Shot! A short ball outside off to start the fresh over. Root goes on the back foot and slashes it past point. It races to the fence.
Kagiso Rabada to bowl from the other end post the Lunch session. 6-0-22-1 so far from him.
Good length ball outside off, Denly stays on the back foot and pushes it towards cover.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked.
First runs off Philander after 33 dot balls. Brilliant stuff so far from Vernon. A good length ball around middle, Root takes a step forward and tucks it towards the leg side for a single.

Beaten! This time he plays the defensive shot but is beaten. Kept slightly low as well. Another good length ball which is in the channel outside off. Root does not move his feet at all and drives to get beaten.
Root was in two minds there. A shortish length ball just outside off, Root first thinks to defend but at the last moment pulls his bat out of the line of the ball.
Good length ball around off, pushed to covers by Root.

We are back for the second session. The South African players are out in the middle. Joe Denly and Joe Root will resume their innings for England. Vernon Philander is marking his run-up and will start the proceedings for the second session.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Now, how will the afternoon session pan out? Will Root and Denly continue adding runs to this stand to take England in a commanding position in the game or will we see the Protea bowlers break the stand and get into the middle-order of England? Join us after the break to find out.

Earlier in the day, England needed only 11 deliveries to get the final wicket of South Africa's innings to bundle them out on 284 runs. Curran who was shy of a wicket could not get the fifer and it was Broad who got the wicket of Philander.

Rabada and Philander started for the Proteas brilliantly with the ball. Philander struck first when he removed Rory Burns in his second over. He has bowled very tight lines and length and has bowled 5 successive maidens. Rabada got rid of Sibley to put England in a troubled situation. Since then, South African bowlers could not manage to get another one. Nortje and Pretorius did bowl well too but without any success. The one over from the spinner was easily negotiated by the English batters.

An even session for both sides then. England though have done well to recover from the early blows, courtesy, a fighting unbeaten stand between Denly and skipper Root. England was in trouble early on when Burns and Sibley departed early without troubling the scorers much. Denly got a life on 0 when Rassie spilled a chance at the first slip. Since then, Denly is looking solid out in the middle and Root too has himself set for a big one.
Length delivery on off, Root pushes it towards covers. The batsmen cross ends. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Outside off, the skipper leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, Denly drives it towards mid on for a run.
Bowls a bumper, Denly ducks under it.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
On a good length on off, Root plays it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Denly offers a forward defense on this one.
Floated delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Keshav Maharaj is into the attack.
Good length delivery on off, Root defends it out.
Bowls a quick bouncer on leg, Root ducks under it. It goes to de Kock who makes a one-handed stop.
On a length on middle, the skipper flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bowls a bouncer, Root does well to duck under it.
On a good length on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Root drives it through point. Maharaj chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good leave now! A ball on a good length and in the channel. Denly covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.

FOUR! Clipped nicely! A good length ball on middle, Denly is very strong there. He flicks it with power and it beats the mid-wicket fielder and races to the fence. He is starting to look settled out in the middle now.
Full and on the stumps, Denly drives it to mid on where Rabada fumbles but no runs taken.
Fuller around off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, it is left alone.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes it away. Very good ball this from Nortje. Pacy and coming in, Root looks to defend but it hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal from the Proteas players but the umpire is not interested. Faf du Plessis does not go for the review as they feel there is a slight inside edge on this.
Length delivery on off, Denly plays it towards covers. The batsmen take a run.
FOUR! Nice shot. Second boundary of the over. Full delivery on middle, Denly drives it through mid on for a boundary. 50 up for England.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Denly looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on middle, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! First one for him. That was boundary the moment it left the bat. A good length on middle, Denly uses his wrists and whips it to deep mid-wicket fence. That raced to the fence in a jiffy.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a good length on off, Root plays it with soft hands and guides it towards third man for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Root punches it to point.
On middle, Root offers a back foot defense on this one.
On a good length on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Root plays it to mid on.
On a good length on off, the skipper defends it off the back foot.
A real spicy delivery this from Nortje. Touches 150kph. It is on the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses. Nortje goes up in appeal but the umpire says no.
Good length delivery outside off, Root taps it towards covers and takes a run.
Short delivery on off, Root cuts it to point.
Good length delivery on middle, Root defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Length delivery outside off, Root goes on the back foot and punches it past the diving gully fielder towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Denly keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Denly blocks it well.
Full delivery on middle, Denly flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on off, Denly looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Denly does not bother to play at that.

FOUR! Educational edge this from Root! A 149 kph delivery bowled on a length around off, Root looks to defend but opens the face of the bat in the last moment to send it wide of the man at gully and the ball races away to the fence.
Outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.

A very intent-ful bouncer but good take from Quinton de Kock. It is around off, Root ducks under it. The ball keeps getting high on de Kock. He jumps, one might feel he even flew there to take it and save runs for his side.
Good length delivery on off, Root taps it to point.
On a good length on off, Root defends it to covers.
Nortje starts with a back of a length ball outside off. He bowls this at 147 kph and makes the ball shoot up off the deck. Root leaves it alone.
Rabada gets a rest Anrich Nortje has been brought back into the attack.
Just away from the stumps. Good length ball on off, Denly looks to defend but he is a bit late on it. It hits the upper part of his bat and rolls behind. It goes past the stumps by just mere inches.
Good length delivery on off, Joe blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the back foot.
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.
On middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off to bowl the first ever ball in Tests from Pretorius. It is left alone.
Debutant Dwaine Pretorius is on.
Denly is off the mark and the crowd applause. A good length ball around off, Denly taps it towards cover. 28th ball it is and Denly has a run.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Sprayed down the leg side. Denly looks to flick but misses.

Dropped! Initially, it looked like it did not carry but it did. Oh, dear! Van der Dussen is the man. Probably de Kock came in the way as he dived to his right to pouch the ball. A brilliant ball from Rabada once again and he cannot believe it as he has his face covered with his hands. A back of a length ball outside off, Denly pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip. De Kock throws himself to his right but cannot reach there. The ball goes in the hands of debutant Rassie but it quickly pops out. It went straight in so one would feel he should've had taken it. Probably the dive of de Kock distracted him there. It can be really costly because Denly can get himself in and play a really big knock.
Good length ball around off and middle, it is defended.
Shortish around middle, pushed to mid on.
Landed around off, Root comes forward and defends. 5 maidens in a row from Philander. He has be so accurate in this spell.
Fuller ball on middle, Denly looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the pads and goes fine leg for of leg byes. Still trying to get off the mark.
Good length ball around off, Denly looks to leave the ball first but is late in removing his bat down. Ends up tapping it towards the off side.
Full and around off, Denly looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Around off, it is defended off the front foot.
Another length delivery outside off, it swings back in after the stumps. Root leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Root does not disturb that.

The physio is out for the concussion test. A routine these days. Root looks absolutely fine but the umpires do not want to take any risks and the concussion test will be conducted. The umpires seize this opportunity and call for drinks as well.

FOUR LEG BYES! But off the helmet. A well directed bouncer from Rabada. Root is late in ducking under it. The ball hits the helmet and goes to to third man fence over the slip cordon. Root takes his helmet off and checks it. He seems fine.
Angled into the batsman this time from a good length. Root looks to tuck it towards the leg side but ends up getting hit high on the thigh pads.
Bumper which goes way to high and it is outside off too. Root shows no interest.
FOUR! Timed superbly! Rabada bowls it full around off, Root comes forward and punches it through point for his first boundary.
Fullish ball inviting for the drive but Denly is not lured into the shot. He lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, Denly makes a leave.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Soft hands again! A good length ball around off, Denly waits for the ball to come to him and defends. The ball takes outside edge and goes towards second slip. The fielder there dives to his right to stop the ball.
Philander was steaming in but the bails fell off at the non-striker's end and the umpire stops the bowler and asks him to steam in again.
Landed around off, it is blocked by Denly. Still searching for that run to get off the mark.
Fuller around off, Denly comes forward and pushes it towards cover.
Shortish ball on off, Root goes on the back foot and defends it out. Testing over this from Rabada.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another play and a miss! A good length ball in the channel outside off, Root once again feels for the ball and goes for the drive. Only to get beaten. Lucky not to edge that one.
A brilliant bouncer now! It is on the body of Root. He hops and looks to fend it away. The ball hits the handle of the bat and goes to fine leg for a couple of runs.

Another peach from Rabada! Fullish ball, closer to off pole. Root without moving his feet pushes at the ball with hard hands. He makes no connection and is beaten for the outside edge. Could've easily gone on to hit the off pole there.
In the channel outside off, Root covers his sticks and lets it be.
Beauty to finish the over! Good length ball around off, the ball zips away a bit. Denly looks to defend but gets beaten.
Away from the off pole, JD shoulders arms to it.
On the fourth stump line, Denly leaves it alone.

Close, close call this. Looks like height has saved Denly. Good length ball pitching on off and middle and jagging back in. Denly looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him over the knee roll and there is a huge appeal. The umpire though does not agree and shakes it away. Faf du Plessis does not review it and it is a good decision as the Hawk Eye later on shows that the ball was going to miss the stumps.
Once again it is on the pads, Denly looks to flick but once again misses.
On the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
England off to a disastrous start and out walks skipper Joe Root to rescue them. Can he help them?

OUT! Caught! Some drama though! Sibley has been given not out by the umpire. Faf du Plessis without even having a word with the bowler signals the 'T' straightaway. However, after he takes the DRS, Sibley starts going off. He did not do that immediately but after the decision has been taken upstairs, he starts walking. The umpire there stops him, probably to get everything confirmed. Now, time for the replays, front foot is okay. And a clear spike on the Ultra Edge. So, now, please keep walking, Mr. Sibley. Coming to the ball, whatta ripper from Rabada. Back of a length ball around off, the right-hander has to play at it. Sibley hops and pokes at the ball but only manages an outside edge to the keeper. England are in all sorts of trouble early on.

Given not out but Faf du Plessis goes for the DRS straightaway. Wait, what? Sibley is walking. He thinks he has nicked it. The umpire stops him and asks him to wait for the confirmation. The confirmation is that there is a clear spike on Ultra Edge. Sibley has to depart.
FOUR! Flicked nicely! First boundary for Sibley! A fullish ball on middle of the right-hander. Sibley is really strong on anything on the pads. He flicks it to the mid-wicket fence nicely.
BEATEN! Good shape on this one! On a good length and outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses it.
Bowls it down the leg side, Sibley lets it go.
Outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on leg, Sibley flicks it towards the leg side.
Length delivery on off, Denly gets right behind the line of the ball and defends it with a straight bat. End of a very successful over from VP.
Back of a length on off, Denly defends it off his back foot.
On the pads, Denly glances it to mid-wicket.
Good ball this. Inswinging from off, JD looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Good length ball outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Joe Denly walks in way too early than he would've thought. 3 slips in place.

OUT! Caught behind! This time there is no need to review it as Burns knows he has got something on it. Absolute jaffa from Vernon Philander. He is one of the best bowler to left-handers and he has struck gold in the very second over here with a peach. Vernon bowls it on a length, in the channel of uncertainty. The ball goes with the angle but then straightens a bit. Rory looks to defend but gets a feather on it of his glove on its way to the keeper. De Kock takes it and goes up in celebration. Burns does not even wait for long and starts walking back. South Africa needed early wicket and they have got just that. Perfect start for Philander in his final series.
On the pads, Burns tucks it to the leg side and keeps the strike.
A good solid front foot defense from Burns. On the stumps, RB blocks it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Rabada is troubling Burns in every possible way here. Full and swinging away. Burns looks to drive it to the on side but gets squared up. It goes off the outside edge through the backward point region for a boundary.
Bouncer! A very well directed one. It is right around his eye line. Burns does well to sway away from it.

Bounce, pace and good carry on this one. Excellent ball. Rabada steams in and hits the deck hard with a 143 kph delivery around off. Burns looks to defend but the ball shapes away squaring Rory all ends up. It shoots on its way to the keeper and reaches Quinton over his head.
Back of a length ball outside off, Burns sways away from it.
Sibley makes another leave as Philander lands this one outside off on a good length.

Just short! Brilliant line this from Philander. A good length ball around off, Sibley this time pokes at the ball but with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to du Plessis at the second slip but on the bounce. Soft hands saved Sibley there.
In the channel outside off, Sibley makes another leave.
Another length ball which is closer to off pole than the previous one but not enough to make Sibley play at it.
Fullish one around off, it is defended.
Philander starts with a good length ball around off, it shapes away from Sibley. He lets it go to the keeper.
Vernon Philander to bowl from the other end.
Just short! Rabada fires one on the pads, Burns looks to flick but it goes off the edge and falls short of the diving man at short leg.
On the pads, Burns once again looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Good length ball outside off, Burns looks to defend but misses.
On the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses and the ball hits the thigh pad.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Superb ball this but Rabada has overstepped here. Full and swinging in on off. Burns looks to play it on the on side but the ball goes off the outside edge through the gully region for a boundary. First runs off the bat.
NO BALL! Poor start for Rabada. After the first ball he has gone way wide outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it. Rabada has overstepped and it has been caught by the umpire.
Wild ball. Length ball way outside off, Burns has no interest in playing that.

NOT OUT! Excellent review and actually the credit has to be given to Sibley. Burns was not sure whether the ball had kissed the bat or not so he reviewed it after having a brief chat with Dominic. South Africa almost had a perfect start just like England. Full and swinging away from the southpaw. Burns looks to drive it straight but misses. There is a noise as the ball goes to the keeper. De Kock takes the catch and goes up in a confident appeal. The umpire agrees and raises his finger. Burns is unsure and has a word with his partner. After consulting Sibley, Rory signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball has missed the bat and the sound is of the bat hitting the pad. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is a very little spike as the ball goes past the bat but there is also a gap so the on-field decision has to be reversed.

So England have a mammoth task in hand if they are to win this game. On a day where they have looked down and out they will need to find a way to lift themselves up in the dressing room and put on a fight. South Africa, on the other hand, are clearly in the driver's seat and without a doubt favourites to take the lead in the series. Can England find a way to rise back from the ashes or will the Proteas roar loud and take a lead in this 4-match Test series. Join us in a short while for England's chase to find out.

England struggled in the field today. They failed to build on the threat they posed on Day 2. They looked lethargic and out of ideas today and illness did not help their case as Jos Buttler and Joe Root struggled to get on the field. The latter did come out but clearly looked at discomfort. Archer was expensive but ended up with a hard fought 5-fer. Stokes was good with the cherry as he got two. Anderson, Broad and Curran looked jaded but ended up with one wicket apiece.

So 376 is the target for England. South Africa will be very happy with their efforts with the bat here. The hosts with a lead of 103 did not get off to a good start in their second innings. Having lost both the openers early, they were stuttering at 165/5 but debutant Rassie van der Dussen and nightwatchman Anrich Nortje took the game away from the visitors with a 91-run stand. Rassie scored his maiden fifty but he could not last long. Anrich Nortje fell 10 short of his fifty. It looked like England could still wrap them up under 300 but Quinton de Kock's counter-attacking 34 took them close to 350. Vernon Philander was also good with the bat as his 46 and Rabada's quickfire 16 in the end took the hosts' lead to a commanding 375.

OUT! CAUGHT! It took a fantastic catch from Jonny Bairstow to end the innings of South Africa. Shorter delivery outside off, Philander looks to play the upper cut  to third man but gets a faint outside edge behind to the keeper. Bairstow leaps high in the air and pouches it with one hand. Terrific stuff. Philander knows that he is out and starts walking off. SOUTH AFRICA ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 272 WITH A LEAD OF 375.
Fullish delivery outside off, Rabada pushes it to deep point and takes a single.
SIX! Rabada is on fire and gives a smile after hitting that! Good length delivery on off, Rabada thrashes it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Full delivery on off, Vernon defends it to point and takes a single.
Bowls a well directed bouncer, Rabada ducks underneath it.
Bowls a bumper, Rabada ducks under it.
FOUR! That is hit with power! Short ball outside off, Rabada stands tall and powers it through covers for a boundary.
Short delivery outside off, Rabada looks to pull but gets a bottom edge on this one. It goes towards the keeper on one bounce.
Length delivery on off, Rabada taps it to point.
Short of a length delivery, Philander looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg where Sam Curran picks the ball on one bounce. The batsmen take a single.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Philander does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on off, Philander taps it towards point for a single.
On a good length on off, Rabada guides it towards third man for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Rabada defends it to point.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a length outside off, Rabada camps back on his back foot and punches it to the deep cover region for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Rabada defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Philander drives it towards mid on. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Rabada works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle, Philander pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Kagiso Rabada is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, the short ball does the trick for England. 5-fer for Archer. Though he has not been at his best and has been expensive, Archer has been the wicket-taking bowler that England were craving for. Short of a length on middle, Maharaj looks to pull but it goes off the top edge towards fine leg. Sam Curran settles himself under it and takes a simple catch. The lead is now 353.
Length delivery on middle, Philander nudges it towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run.
Short delivery on leg, Maharaj pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Philander tucks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Length delivery on middle, Philander flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single. The lead is now 350 for South Africa.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander lets it sail through to the keeper.

Drinks! South Africa are leading this game by a mile now. Since the Lunch break, they have lost only 1 wicket and have swelled their lead to 345 runs. That lead is very good on this wicket. England, on the other hand, are looking down and out. They are in need of something special if they have to make a comeback in this game. It looks highly difficult. Will they be able to do it?
On a length on middle, Philander flicks it through square leg for a run.

Full delivery on middle, Philander drives it through mid on for a run.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander ducks under it.
Good length delivery on off, Maharaj looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a run.
On a good length on off, Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Philander blocks it off the front foot.
Short delivery on middle, Maharaj pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
On a good length on middle, Maharaj plays it towards mid on.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Maharaj looks to defend but misses it.

FOUR! Wow! What a shot! Length ball outside off, Maharaj lofts it over covers for a boundary. Naseer Hussain on air says he is better than a tail-ender in his opinion and one can hardly argue with that. He is no walkover with the bat.
On a length on middle, Philander flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
WIDE! Bowls it wide outside off, Philander offers no shot to this one.
Sam Curran is back on. 9-3-25-0 are his figures so far.
Short delivery on off, Philander plays it towards point for a run.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander ducks underneath it.

Ouch! That's hit him right on the box. Everyone knows how painful that is. Vernon is wincing in pain. Good length ball around off, Philander looks to push but gets an inside edge and the ball goes and hits him flush in the unmentionables.

Length delivery on off, Philander taps it towards point for a run.
On a length on off, Philander defends it towards covers for a single.
Length delivery on off, Vernon taps it to point.
On a length on middle, Philander flicks it to mid-wicket.
